reviewText: The upside is that Brooks Williams is an excellent teacher.  The downside is that there is precious little here with respect to his body of work, you get to learn basically two songs, and that's it.  It would be nice to have an extended disc, or added online content, as he is so prolific.  Having said that, both of these have made it into my "campfire playlist", and I'll be playing them a lot this year.
